io.github.struppigel.parser.sections.idata

Enum DelayLoadDirectoryKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DelayLoadDirectoryKey>
      • io.github.struppigel.parser.sections.idata.DelayLoadDirectoryKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HeaderKey, FieldOrStructureKey, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DelayLoadDirectoryKey>

    public enum DelayLoadDirectoryKey
extends java.lang.Enum<DelayLoadDirectoryKey>
implements HeaderKey
    Represents keys for the delay-load directory table.

    Descriptions are taken from the PE/COFF specification.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      ATTRIBUTES
      Must be zero
      BOUND_DELAY_IMPORT_TABLE

      DELAY_IMPORT_NAME_TABLE
      The RVA of the delay-load name table, which contains the names of the imports that might need to be loaded.

      NAME
      The RVA of the name of the DLL to be loaded.
      TIME_STAMP
      The timestamp of the DLL to which this image has been bound.
      UNLOAD_DELAY_IMPORT_TABLE
      The RVA of the unload delay-load address table, if it exists.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ATTRIBUTES

        public static final DelayLoadDirectoryKey ATTRIBUTES
        Must be zero

      • NAME

        public static final DelayLoadDirectoryKey NAME
        The RVA of the name of the DLL to be loaded. The name resides in the read-only data section of the image

      • MODULE_HANDLE

        public static final DelayLoadDirectoryKey MODULE_HANDLE
        The RVA of the module handle (in the data section of the image) of the DLL to be delay-loaded. It is used for storage by the routine that is supplied to manage delay-loading.

      • DELAY_IAT

        public static final DelayLoadDirectoryKey DELAY_IAT
        The RVA of the delay-load import address table.

      • DELAY_IMPORT_NAME_TABLE

        public static final DelayLoadDirectoryKey DELAY_IMPORT_NAME_TABLE
        The RVA of the delay-load name table, which contains the names of the imports that might need to be loaded. This matches the layout of the import name table.

      • BOUND_DELAY_IMPORT_TABLE

        public static final DelayLoadDirectoryKey BOUND_DELAY_IMPORT_TABLE
        The RVA of the bound delay-load address table, if it exists.

      • UNLOAD_DELAY_IMPORT_TABLE

        public static final DelayLoadDirectoryKey UNLOAD_DELAY_IMPORT_TABLE
        The RVA of the unload delay-load address table, if it exists. This is an exact copy of the delay import address table. If the caller unloads the DLL, this table should be copied back over the delay import address table so that subsequent calls to the DLL continue to use the thunking mechanism correctly.

      • TIME_STAMP

        public static final DelayLoadDirectoryKey TIME_STAMP
        The timestamp of the DLL to which this image has been bound.
